hopobject.body: I'm not interested in football buy enalapril maleate His interim Prime Minister Hazem el-Beblawi said that to “restore security” they had no choice but to break up the protest camps: “This had to happen, everything was done in plain sight for everyone to see and hear what was happening. Everything was videoed. It could be seen that there were weapons and ammunition. This was not just a sit-in two in these two places – Nahda and Rabaa al-Adawiya – rather we felt that there was a campaign to create disorder. There have been attacks against police stations, government buildings, hospitals, so the state had to intervene and take these exceptional measures.”
